description: Manage tunnel interfaces of a load balancer.

commands.name: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface add
commands.summary: Add one tunnel interface into the load balance tunnel interface pool.
commands.syntax:
az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface add --address-pool
                                                --identifier
                                                --lb-name
                                                --protocol {Native, None, VXLAN}
                                                --resource-group
                                                --type {External, Internal, None}
                                                [--index]
                                                [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                [--port]
examples: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface add -g MyResourceGroup --lb-name MyLb --address-pool MyAddressPool --type external --protocol vxlan --identifier 901 --port 10000

commands.name: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface list
commands.summary: List all tunnel interfacees of the load balance tunnel interface pool.
commands.syntax:
az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface list --address-pool
                                                 --lb-name
                                                 --resource-group
examples: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface list -g MyResourceGroup --lb-name MyLb --address-pool MyAddressPool

commands.name: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface remove
commands.summary: Remove one tunnel interface from the load  balance tunnel interface pool.
commands.syntax:
az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface remove --address-pool
                                                   --index
                                                   --lb-name
                                                   --resource-group
                                                   [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
examples: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface remove -g MyResourceGroup --lb-name MyLb --address-pool MyAddressPool --index 0

commands.name: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface show
commands.summary: Get one tunnel interface of load balance tunnel interface pool.
commands.syntax:
az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface show --address-pool
                                                 --index
                                                 --lb-name
                                                 --resource-group
examples: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface show -g MyResourceGroup --lb-name MyLb --address-pool MyAddressPool --index 0

commands.name: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface update
commands.summary: Update one tunnel interface of load balance tunnel interface pool.
commands.syntax:
az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface update --address-pool
                                                   --index
                                                   --lb-name
                                                   --resource-group
                                                   [--add]
                                                   [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                   [--identifier]
                                                   [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                   [--port]
                                                   [--protocol {Native, None, VXLAN}]
                                                   [--remove]
                                                   [--set]
                                                   [--type {External, Internal, None}]
examples: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface update -g MyResourceGroup --lb-name MyLb --address-pool MyAddressPool --type external --protocol vxlan --identifier 901 --port 10000 --index 0

commands.name: az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
commands.syntax:
az network lb address-pool tunnel-interface wait [--address-pool]
                                                 [--created]
                                                 [--custom]
                                                 [--deleted]
                                                 [--exists]
                                                 [--ids]
                                                 [--interval]
                                                 [--lb-name]
                                                 [--resource-group]
                                                 [--subscription]
                                                 [--timeout]
                                                 [--updated]
